    "title": "In My Mind, Two Roads Diverged......",
    "description": "&quot;Ships that pass in the night, and speak each other in passing,\nOnly a signal shown and a distant voice in the darkness:\nSo on the ocean of life, we pass and speak one another,\nOnly a look and a voice, then darkness again and a silence.&quot;\n– Henry Wadsworth Longfellow, &quot;Tales of a Wayside Inn&quot; (1863-1874),\n\n&quot;All individuals of the &quot;higher&quot; insects — the butterflies and moths (Lepidopteral), flies and mosquitoes (Dipteral), and wasps, ants, and bees (Hy-menopteral) — along with many amphibians, invertabrates, and fish, undergo drastic change during their life cycles when they metamorphose from larva to adult.&quot;\n– Mary Jane West-Eberhard, &quot;Developmental Plasticity and Evolution&quot;",
